<br />

<br />
The "significant part" of a tank's job is not to stand there and take a beating, it is to hold the mob's attention while the rest of the crew does their thing. The beating part is a side effect of that job.
<br />

<br />
As such, a pet can NEVER outperform a pc tank. EVER. Why? Because npcs can and never will be able to overaggro a PC. You could give my pet the mitigation of a Time+ warrior, the AC of a Time+ warrior, 100k hp, and it still won't mean SHIT when that level 59 ranger decides he'd rather play "poke the bad thing with the stick"....he will STILL get torn a new one by the mob.
<br />

<br />
All of this rhetoric about the fear of pets outperforming tanks has its roots in a SINGLE motivation: to FORCE casters to seek out melees and rely on them for any noticable gain in the game. I don't know why, but the idea of mages, enchanters, necros, wizards, druids, clerics, and shamen banding together in something other than Healer/Tank/slower(utility)/dps/dps/dps scares the living JESUS out of melees and hybrids. Which is sad, because said classes already find a way around that, some having greater success than others.
<br />

<br />
Oh...as for your original comments...question:
<br />

<br />
Do you frown on soloing?
<br />
Do you frown on the whole chanter/charm thing?
<br />

<br />
