				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">ok, first off Rylden  has my vote for class correspondent. We need someone in this position that is as stubborn as they are :o) 
<br />

<br />
I still feel that this job is important because this is the person that directs our concerns to SOE. Even if SOE never changes a thing about this game we still have someone annoying the crap out of them LOL!
<br />

<br />
As for the pet tank issue I think that no pet should be able to have the AC or HP of a warrior but with that said there is more to being a good tank in this game then just pulling and hitting Auto attack and taunt. You will find some in this game that are like that but if you want to play a good tank you have to do more.
<br />

<br />
I have always throught that my pet should be able to off-tank the mobs. I think that groups should not be forced to rely on tank classes in order to form a group. Anyone who has read my post over the years knows that I am far from a fan of the "holy trinity" and my girlfriend plays an Enchanter.
<br />

<br />
My feeling is simple. There is what 15 classes in this game. Make the game around 15 classes and not around 3 or 4. If I want to take my Mage and go out and group with a BL and a druid we should be able to and not have to rely on the "key" classes in EQ in order to get experience. 
<br />

<br />
The restrictions on what can work at high lvls of the game has always been one of this games downfalls. I am hoping that one day they will have the sense to fix it. You want me to have to group? Ok, I can live with that but do not make me "Have to have" an enchanter or shaman, Warrior, and a cleric. If I want to get together and group with my buddies and we are all pure casters we should be able to do that and get experience. That would make this game a lot more appealing.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and I plan on sticking with this game. I have no intention of switching over to EQ 2 or any other game for at least the next five months or so. I still like to play this game even with all of it's faults and I hope you guys stick with it. 
<br />

<br />
Ravenspire Merquise-lvl 64 Arch Mage and proud member of Asatru of Povar</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
