			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A pet is an acceptable way to hold off a mob to burn it down. It is all it is for. It holds it off for you to kill the mob. There is no thought process, no finess. It is what the class was designed to do from day 1 of EQ. A pet to take the beating for the mage, and the mage have a chance to win. You have no escape but run or gate. The mage pet was effective in that capacity in original EQ, Kunark, and less in Velious as we got no new pets, and went down hill faster in SoL where again we got no new pets, our spell based damage was still eclipsed by the Kunark era bolt, and other classes got bigger dd then us (see moonfire for a druid, who now out nuked us, had heals and buffs, ports, snare, root, dire charm, etc..), mages fell to the way side in SoV and accelerated downhill fast in SoL. Pets were never going to replace a tank, but people feared it and the class floundered and so few mages were left. 
<br />

<br />
The trend is now that in a major expansions we get pets for the previous major expansion. PoP era pets would have been about right for SoL expansion. PoP should have seen us with OOW era pets, and OOW pets should be better then they are now.
<br />

<br />
Calebe<br />_________________<br />Level 70 Magician
<br />
E'CI Server
<br />
Infinit</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
