<br />

<br />
Ever heard of agro management? If I let CoW melee a lvl 65 named in NC down to 85% before starting nukes I can chain cast SV from there down to mob death and not draw agro. BoJ is almost double the damage and double the agro. If I decide to be a <img src="images/smiles/dink.gif" alt="" border="0" />, I can pull agro off my raid MT with BoJ even if I wait for the attack call (Time+ geared with Time agro-weap, all the relevant proc AAs etc). 
<br />

<br />
CoW is an EXTREMELY good tank. Better than many equivalent level Warriors and knights. My lvl 60 shammy-bot can safely chain cast Slow, cripple and Bane of Nife as soon as the first air pet stun goes off (resisted or not). The shammy draws agro occassionally, but he only needs to back up once CoW get back into melee range as it will have taken agro again.
<br />

