<br />
You must play with some really crappy level 67 players. How do they react when you mention the word "eBay" to them?
<br />

<br />
You do know that level 67 players aren't allowed in Riftseekers' or Anguish no matter how good their gear is? For that matter, we'd rather go one or two players short in a group most anywhere than take a poorly-geared level 67 player with us.
<br />

<br />
Yes, CoW holds aggro reasonably well for casters, and for casters only, and aggro management is a skill that is important in the game for all players.
<br />

<br />
No, CoW or any other pet, can never hold aggro over a melee PC attacking the mob.
<br />

<br />
No, CoW still can't mitigate/aviod as well as even equivalent <span style="font-style: italic">level </span>warriors or knights and certainly can't do anything at all intelligent that is needed from a tank, such as pulling mobs off healers, moving off-tanked mobs away from the group, allowing PCs to melee, or even dealing with enrage (yes, you can have it dumbly stand there, but it isn't going to taunt to maintian aggro).
<br />

<br />
Worse yet, the OoW pets scale <span style="font-style: italic">worse </span>with gear than did the PoP pets. OoW pets are nowhere near your melee <span style="font-style: italic">peers </span>in ability.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Elementalist Itchyban of Veeshan</a>
